| V | 8.3 | 17.5 | 16.8 | 17.5 | 39.9 | 100 |
| VI | 5.3 | 13.3 | 16.3 | 20.3 | 44.8 | 100 |
| VII | 3.5 | 10.0 | 14.0 | 21.5 | 51.0 | 100 |
| VIII | 2.5 | 7.5 | 12.3 | 19.3 | 58.4 | 100 |

Each row shows the variation in children's reading levels within a given grade. For example, among children in Std III, 21.6% cannot even read a letter, 28.6% can read a letter but not a word, 17.4% can read a word but not a Std I level text, 11.7% can read a Std I level text but not a Std II level text, and 20.7% can read a Std II level text. For each grade, the total of these exclusive categories is 100%.

